caption: I had a wonderful experience at Doozy's Subs & Pizza Shop here in downtown Omaha , Nebraska this afternoon 😄. This was my first time dining at this diner and I 'm happy that I came in to have lunch . I encourage everyone to come and enjoy both the atmosphere and the food 😊.
excellent service and food
Fantastic toasted subs.
Great food, great prices
I love their sandwiches. Customer service is great as well.
This is my favorite sandwich shop in downtown Omaha. I really enjoy their pasta bakes as well. Great place for lunch.
Order on Friday at 230 got there and they are closed even for takeout

I called to get lunch because I forgot mine and wanted to try something new.  Asked if they delivered and they were willing to bring it to me as I do not work very far. Poor guy went to the wrong federal building and I believe that was my mistake. He huffed it to get to me. I appreciate that. Thank you Doozys! The food was excellent at well. Will order again
I love there subs
Great food, friendly staff.

Great food, fast service.
Hard to pick a favorite sandwich, they are all so good!
A solid sandwich every time! Got the half Italian with half am order of cheese bread. My only regret, not getting the full order of cheese bread! So good!
Clean place, prompt service, great sandwiches. Try the Italian Combo!
Highly recommend, excellent food and service every time I go in.
Portion size is perfect and food is delicious! 😋
Good value, good food, good service. Didn't blow my skirt up, but always a solid option if you're wondering where to eat. Buffalo chicken pizza is tasty.
Delicious pizza and buffalo chicken sandwich, employees were super friendly
Just ate here for the first time, staff was very friendly. Wait for my sandwich was super short. The sandwich itself was delicious, I'll definitely be stopping in again. Thanks!
I ordered the smothered chicken sub....SO DELICIOUS! And the owner is always friendly and welcoming
Really good subs here!!
The pasta bakes are delicious!!!!!
Doozy's is always fast, tasty, and reliable. Love it!
kind of a no nonsense type of guy taking the order. I can see how some people would be put off by him, but I thought food was really good.

Great food that meets my expectations every time!
Great little shop with good prices. Try the buffalo chicken sandwich or the Hot Jake.
Awesome pizza
Good subs. Love the option for a snack size
Great pasta bakes.  Prompt service.  One of my go to's for lunch

Good food. Owner is as nice as can be. The older lady and younger lady seem to care less about customer service and more about being rude than anything else. My advice is if you see the older man at the counter, stop in and enjoy some good sandwiches.  If not keep walking and 2njoy better customer service elsewhere.
Great food, clean, and great service
Small place but decent pasta bakes and sandwiches!
One of the best lunch spots downtown. Consistently good food.
Best subs in downtown. The sub's are so good that the store is almost always full despite having subway in the next block.
Great sandwiches, fast service. They also have thin crust pizzas, salads, and pasta bakes. Make sure to order the Hot Jake off the secret menu for an extra kick in your lunch. It's a doozy!
Fantastic sandwiches, lots of options to choose from.
Fast and delicious
Although the subs are great you have to try the pizzas. Some of the best food in Omaha!!
Love the pizza and the girls I was with enjoyed the chicken salad and the sub sandwich

Absolutely a great sandwich been eatin em for years and its is the best on market -  hands down !!!!!!!
Great lunch prices, but I feel they are a little skimpy on the meat in their sandwiches. Everything tasted good, staff was friendly enough. The sandwiches always left something to be desired.
SO many choices for subs and pizzas! I got the taco pizza and it was very good. The crust is a nice medium between thin and regular. Good pricing and the employees are friendly.

Comfortable food, casual atmosphere, quick service.
Friendly staff and excellent food. Lots of sandwhich choices. Plus pizza and pasta.
I hear the food is really good. There aren't any gluten free options.

Doozy's is a great option for lunch! Their bread is to die for, and you can get a combo with chips and a drink for about $7. The staff is friendly and the have tons of sandwiches to choose from. My personal favorite is the club sandwich!

This place is both dope and legit. I eat lunch here about twice a week. The buffalo chicken sandwich is the best. Great fresh baked bread. The staff is super nice too. I'm always so puzzled by people eating Picklman's or Jimmy Johns. For less money, they could get a way better sandwich at Doozy's just a block away.
Great pizza!

Went for lunch (first visit).  The cashier was very helpful.  She recommended the Red Meat Sauce pasta bake.  It was very good.  Price was reasonable and the quantity was appropriate for lunch.  The subs coming out of the kitchen looked delicious.  I'll definitely go back to try some more of the items.  If you need a "pasta fix" in the Old Market around lunch time this would be a good place to check out.
This place sells the dankest sandwich in Nebraska hands down
Everything is tasty!   Good food for a good price!
The sandwiches are so good!

I didn't eat here. I called in an order of two pizzas from Minnesota, and Doozy's delivered them to a rather tough to find office complex on the other side of downtown for my girlfriend! She told me the pizza was great!
Amazing sandwiches and amazing owner!

This place was GREAT. I got a gift certificate to this place and will definitely be coming back again now. The steak and cheese sub was delicious. Loved the staff as well. It felt very welcoming. Recommend 100%.
Unusually bad food served with pride at twice the price. Causes serious digestion issues. Bread is like a cork, it will clog you up for days.
One of the best Sub shops in town.. Steak and Cheese = soooo good.. but the Chicken bacon ranch with Green Peppers = AMAZING.. Staff is wonderful. Fast delivery. The owner, Jerry, he is the man!
